JO  - AMJ
SP  - 316
EP  - 329
VL  - 6
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses the challenges of teaching the science and theory of management. The author creates an analogy of the management theory jungle and compares the teaching of management science to the training soldiers for jungle warfare. A discussion is presented about the nature of management both as a discipline and as an art. The author presents an overview of contributions made to the field of management from different sciences and speculates on the future of management theory in the United States.
