VL  - 6
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article reports on an experiment which aimed to evaluate management development programs administered in a given organization. The author describes the methodology of the developmental effort and presents findings of the study as they relate to both supervisors and subordinate employees. A discussion is presented about the implications of the study's findings as it relates to the management of a variety of organizations. An overview of related research focused on management training is presented.
